  {
    "page": 6,
    "block_id": "page_006:block_017",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "Figure 2 shows an overview of Simple-SZZ-Agent. Given a fix com- mit, the approach collects the commit histories of all files modi- fied by the fix, forming a single candidate set. It then provides an LLM-based agent with the fix commit message, the fix commit diff, and the full candidate set. The agent has access to standard devel- oper tools (file reading, grep, glob) and is instructed to identify the bug-introducing commit. Since our ablations showed that omitting binary search improves both performance and cost (RQ2e), and that Stage 1 alone contributes less than Stage 2 (RQ2d), Simple-SZZ- Agent removes both: no SZZ-based filtering, no binary search, and no multi-stage pipeline—it relies entirely on the agent to find the bug-introducing commit among all candidates.",
    "bbox": [
      53.15299987792969,
      453.87982177734375,
      295.5602722167969,
      586.8193969726562
    ],
    "reading_order": 17,
